'''Bury EMU Depot''' was an Electric Traction Depot located in [[Bury, Greater Manchester|Bury]], [[Manchester]], England. The depot was located on the west side of the line to the south of [[Bury railway station]].<ref>{{harvnb|Webster|Greengrass|Greaves|1987|p=16}}</ref>

The depot code was BQ.

== History ==
Originally a steam facility known as Buckley Wells depot, it was closed between 1965 and 1973. By 1983, [[British Rail Class 504|Class 504]] [[electric multiple unit|EMU]]s had been allocated to the depot.<ref>{{harvnb|Anon.|1983|p=50}}</ref> The depot is now used by the [[East Lancashire Railway]].

