[[File:Immigrate - en Naturalisatiedienst loket Bergstraat, Utrecht (2018) 02.jpg|thumb|right|Immigrate - en Naturalisatiedienst loket Bergstraat, Utrecht (2018) 02|An office of the Immigration and Naturalisation Service in [[Utrecht (city)|Utrecht]].]]

The '''Immigration and Naturalisation Service''', Dutch: ''Immigratie en Naturalisatiedienst'' (IND), is a [[Netherlands|Dutch]] [[government agency]] that handles the admission of [[alien (law)|foreigners]] in the Netherlands. It is part of the [[Ministry of Security and Justice (Netherlands)|Ministry of Security and Justice]]. The IND processes all applications for [[right of asylum|asylum]], [[family reunification]], [[visa (document)|visas]], and other residence permits.

On behalf of the Dutch Deputy Minister of Security and Justice (since 2015 [[Klaas Dijkhoff]]) the IND implements the [[alien (law)|aliens]] [[policy]], the aliens [[Act of Parliament|act]] (Dutch: 'Vreemdelingenwet') and the Netherlands [[nationality]] act (Dutch: 'Rijkswet op het Nederlanderschap').

