'''Maximiliano Cipriano Jones''' (1871–1944) was a [[Fernandinos#II. Krio Fernandinos|Krio Fernandino]] who became the richest black planter of the island [[Fernando Po (island)|Fernando Po]], [[Spanish Guinea]] in 1929.<ref>From slaving to neoslavery: the bight of Biafra and Fernando Po in the era of abolition, 1827-1930; by I. K. Sundiata; Univ of Wisconsin Press, 1996; {{ISBN|0-299-14510-7}}, {{ISBN|978-0-299-14510-1}}; p.158</ref>

==Legacy==

His son, [[Wilwardo Jones]], was also a planter on the island.

