The '''Oddaverjar''' were among the most powerful family clans in the medieval [[Icelandic Commonwealth]]. They were based in [[Oddi]] at [[Rangárvellir]] in South Iceland. Their ascendancy was during the second half of the 12th century, but their power subsequently waned.  They play only a minor role in the Icelandic civil war during the [[Age of the Sturlungs]].  Only after the signing of the ''[[Old Covenant (Iceland)|Gamli sáttmáli]]'' ("Old Covenant") did they oppose the influence of [[Gissur Þorvaldsson]], Earl of Iceland.

The Oddverjar traced their roots to the first Icelandic settlers.  The first known Oddaverji was ''[[Sæmundur Sigfússon]] fróði''  ("Sæmundur The Knowledgeable"), an early 12th century scholar.

