{{Infobox musical artist <!-- For individuals; see Wikipedia:WikiProject_Musicians --> | name = Umeko Ando | image = Umeko Ando.jpg | caption = | image_size = | background = solo_singer | birth_name = | alias = | birth_date = {{Birth date|1932|11|20}} | death_date = {{Death date and age|2004|07|15|1932|11|20}} | origin = Husikokotan, [[Obihiro, Hokkaidō|Obihiro]], [[Hokkaidō]], [[Japan]] | instrument = [[Mukkuri]] | genre = [[Ainu music|Ainu]] | occupation = | years_active = 1960–2003 | label = | associated_acts = [[Oki (musician)|OKI]] | website = }}
{{Nihongo|'''Umeko Ando'''|安東 ウメ子|Andō Umeko|extra=November 20, 1932{{spaced ndash}} July 15, 2004}} was an [[Ainu people|Ainu]] [[singer]] and [[mukkuri]] player. In addition to recording several albums, often with [[Oki (musician)|Oki Kano]], she is featured posthumously on the ''[[Samurai Champloo]]'' soundtrack with her song {{nihongo|"Pekambe Uk"|ペカンベ ウㇰ||"Wheat Harvesting Song"}}. The seventeenth episode, which featured this song, was dedicated in her memory.
